HOSPITAL COURSE

Summary Written by: Date
The patient was admitted for complications arising from Diabetes. During the course of stabilization and care, it was determined that a root cause of her continued diabetic complications was the inability to afford and get access to healthy food. Nutrition education sessions were provided and a referral to Senior Farmers' Market Nutrition Program was made. This program is convenient to her and will provide additional health food access as well as social supports, companionship and nutrition education. Bernie Burns, MD 06/18/2021 11:59 AM
